	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Super Mario Galaxy for Wii has such a "Co-Star mode": player 2 can shoot candy at enemies with the Wii Remote. I'd like to see a hack of SMB1 to freeze bad guys by shooting coins at enemies with the Zapper. Then the Koopas would really be <a href="http://pineight.com/mw/index.php?title=Jump_on_the_duck" class="postlink">ducks</a>.
<br />
<br />In Sonic 2 for Sega Genesis, Tails can't get hurt.
<br />
<br />In Kirby Super Star for Super NES, player 2 can regenerate at will at the cost of a change in power.
<br />
<br />In Chip n Dale Rescue Rangers for NES, one rodent can carry the other across the hard parts.
<br />
<br />There are probably bunches of Game Genie codes for infinite player 2 lives in games like Contra, TMNT 2/3, etc.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


